title: Laranjeira (Rua da)
body:
It was the part of the current Rua do Carmo between the church of the same name and the Ribeirinho bridge, near the Rego alley.
The chapel of Santo António was located on Rua da Laranjeira, and its founder and year of construction are unknown. It was ordered to be demolished by the City Council on February 5, 1836.

1836: Demolition of the chapel of Santo António on Rua da Laranjeira
